  "Initiated By" : "NATIONAL FUTURES ASSOCIATION",
  "Allegations" : "NFA CASE NO. 10-BCC-008, MARCH 10, 2010: THE NATIONAL FUTURES ASSOCIATION (\"NFA\") ISSUED A COMPLAINT CHARGING ROBERT WESLEY BROOKE WITH FAILURE TO SUPERVISE IN VIOLATION OF NFA COMPLIANCE RULE 2-9(A).  AT ALL TIMES RELEVANT TO THE COMPLAINT, BROOKE WAS A PRINCIPAL AND ASSOCIATED PERSON (\"AP\") OF A NFA MEMBER FIRM THAT WAS A COMMODITY POOL OPERATOR (\"CPO\").  BROOKE WAS ALSO AN NFA ASSOCIATE.  THE NFA ALLEGED THAT BROOKE WAS A LISTED PRINCIPAL OF AN NFA MEMBER WELL AS AN AP OF THE FIRM DURING THE PERIOD RELEVANT TO THIS COMPLAINT.  AS SUCH, BROOKE WAS OBLIGATED UNDER NFA'S COMPLIANCE RULES TO SUPERVISE DILIGENTLY THE NFA MEMBER'S EMPLOYEES AND AGENTS IN THE CONDUCT OF THEIR FUTURES AND FOREX BUSINESS ON BEHALF OF THE FIRM.  THE DILIGENT SUPERVISION OF EMPLOYEES AND AGENTS IN THEIR ACTIVITIES FOR OR ON BEHALF OF AN NFA MEMBER, IN PART, REQUIRES THE NFA MEMBER'S ASSOCIATES WHO HAVE SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES, TO ENSURE THAT THE MEMBER ADHERES TO NFA COMPLIANCE RULES GOVERNING THE USE AND CONTENT OF PROMOTIONAL MATERIAL.",
  "Resolution" : "Order",
  "SanctionDetails" : [ {
    "Sanctions" : "Civil and Administrative Penalty(ies)/Fine(s)",
    "SanctionDetails" : [ {
      "Amount" : "$75,000.00"
    } ]
  } ],
  "Broker Comment" : "THE HEARING PANEL MADE NO FINDINGS OF ANY VIOLATIONS BY BROOKE OR HIS FIRM. THE HEARING PANEL ORDERED THAT IF BROOKE WERE TO APPLY FOR NFA MEMBERSHIP, ASSOCIATE NFA MEMBERSHIP OR PRINCIPAL STATUS WITH AN NFA MEMBER IN THE FUTURE, HE WILL HAVE TO PAY A FINE OF $75,000 PRIOR TO SUCH REGISTRATION BECOMING EFFECTIVE."
}

